results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
My First Feather-Legged Fly
This was a brand new species for me.  You can see where it gets its name.  It was on Queen Anne's lace which will continue to bloom right up until a hard freeze.  Neat feathering on the hind legs.
A female
